BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
PRODID:-//Springshare//LibCal//EN
CALSCALE:GREGORIAN
METHOD:PUBLISH
X-WR-CALNAME:Library Workshops
X-WR-CALDESC:The Library hosts workshops on topics such as getting started 
 with reference managers\, using AI tools for research and writing\, 
 managing and sharing your research data\, and more. \n\n Regular sessions 
 include: \n\n\n    Kickstart Your Writing with AI\n  Zotero Basics\n  
 EndNote Basics\n  Cleaning Data with OpenRefine\n  Using DMPTool to Prepare 
 your Data Management and Sharing Plan\n\nOur workshops are hosted regularly 
 from September through June. We can also work with you to schedule small 
 group sessions on demand. Contact us  to discuss your needs with an OHSU 
 Library expert\, or to suggest topics for future sessions.
X-WR-TIMEZONE:America/Los_Angeles
X-PUBLISHED-TTL:PT15M
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260213T200000Z
DTEND:20260213T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260213T000000Z
SUMMARY:Consensus Deep Search: Dive into the Literature with Generative AI
DESCRIPTION:Learn how Consensus uses AI to find and analyze scholarly 
 literature by identifying key claims\, supporting evidence\, and research 
 gaps. This workshop introduces the Consensus platform and examines how 
 AI-driven retrieval influences what information appears\, how it’s 
 ranked\, and how these insights can inform your research process. 
 Participants will also reflect on the opportunities and challenges of using 
 generative AI in academic research. \n\nBy the end of this session\, 
 learners will be able to:\n\n\n	Describe the strengths and limitations of 
 generative AI-assisted search tools\n	Identify OHSU policies related to the 
 use of publicly available generative AI tools\n	Use the features of 
 Consensus for scholarly literature searching\n	Analyze the implications of 
 Consensus’s search coverage and functionality\n	Compare Consensus to 
 similar AI tools\n\n\nOHSU users have subscription access to Consensus if 
 they register at Consensus.app with their OHSU email address.\n\nThis 
 workshop will be recorded\, and the recording will be shared with all 
 registered attendees after the session. If you cannot make the workshop 
 date and time\, you are welcome to register in order to receive a copy of 
 the recording.
LOCATION:Virtual
ORGANIZER;CN="Laura Zeigen":MAILTO:zeigenl@ohsu.edu
CATEGORIES:AI
UID:LibCal-6248-15739313
URL:https://librarycalendar.ohsu.edu/event/15739313
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260218T200000Z
DTEND:20260218T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260218T000000Z
SUMMARY:Zotero Basics
DESCRIPTION:Zotero is a popular\, freely available reference managment 
 tool. Sign up for this hands-on workshop to learn how to use it!\n\nWe will 
 cover:\n\n\n	How to build and organize a Zotero Library\n	How to use Zotero 
 to find full text PDFs for articles via the OHSU Library Catalog\n	How to 
 use the Zotero Add-in for Microsoft Word to create and format citations and 
 bibliographies\n\n\nPrerequisites:\n\n\n	Please visit the Zotero download 
 page to download and install the desktop client and install the Zotero 
 Connector in your preferred web browser.\n
LOCATION:Virtual
ORGANIZER;CN="Marijane White":MAILTO:whimar@ohsu.edu
CATEGORIES:Citation and Reference Management
UID:LibCal-6248-16043881
URL:https://librarycalendar.ohsu.edu/calendar/workshops/zotero-feb-2026
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260220T190000Z
DTEND:20260220T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260220T000000Z
SUMMARY:Truth or Fiction? Verifying AI-Generated Answers
DESCRIPTION:Generative artificial intelligence tools like ChatGPT can 
 produce convincing answers\, but not all of them are based on reliable 
 sources. In this hands-on workshop\, you’ll learn how to write balanced 
 prompts to reduce bias in answers generated by common AI chatbots such as 
 ChatGPT\, and how to fact-check those responses using proven information 
 literacy strategies. This session will demonstrate practical skills to use 
 AI chatbots responsibly and verify the accuracy of the text they 
 generate.\n\nAfter the session\, learners will be able to:\n\n\n	Craft 
 effective prompts for use with public generative AI chatbots such as 
 ChatGPT\, Gemini\, Claude\, etc.\n	Describe the strengths and limitations 
 of generative AI for information search and retrieval\n	Use information 
 literacy skills and tools to evaluate AI-generated text output\n\n\nThis 
 workshop will be recorded\, and the recording will be shared with all 
 registered attendees after the session. If you cannot make the workshop 
 date and time\, you are welcome to register in order to receive a copy of 
 the recording.
LOCATION:Virtual
ORGANIZER;CN="David Carson":MAILTO:carsondav@ohsu.edu
CATEGORIES:AI
UID:LibCal-6248-15730834
URL:https://librarycalendar.ohsu.edu/event/15730834
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260220T200000Z
DTEND:20260220T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260220T000000Z
SUMMARY:PubMed Essentials: Save Time and Find Better Results
DESCRIPTION:Make the most of PubMed for your research! This hands-on 
 workshop will introduce strategies for efficient and effective searching\, 
 helping you save time and find higher-quality evidence. You'll learn how to 
 use PubMed to construct more precise searches with more relevant results. 
 We will also talk about methods to mitigate biases in your search\, and 
 some tips on leveraging AI to help enrich your search strategy. Whether you 
 are new to information research or looking to sharpen your search 
 expertise\, this session will equip you with practical skills to improve 
 your research process. \n\nBy the end of this session\, learners will be 
 able to:\n\n\n	Use features of PubMed for efficient and effective 
 searching\, including crafting advanced Boolean queries \n	Use PubMed 
 accounts to save searches and create search alerts\n	Evaluate contextual 
 authority and bias in PubMed and related tools and revise searches to 
 mitigate those biases\n\n\nThis workshop will be recorded\, and the 
 recording will be shared with all registered attendees after the session. 
 If you cannot make the workshop date and time\, you are welcome to register 
 in order to receive a copy of the recording.
LOCATION:Virtual
ORGANIZER;CN="Kristin Whitman":MAILTO:whitmank@ohsu.edu
CATEGORIES:PubMed
UID:LibCal-6248-15847861
URL:https://librarycalendar.ohsu.edu/event/15847861
END:VEVENT
