BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260506T190000Z
DTEND:20260506T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260506T000000Z
SUMMARY:Completing the NIH Biosketch: SciENcv Common Form & Supplement
DESCRIPTION:Beginning January 25\, 2026\, NIH is replacing the current 
 biosketch with a two-part format: a Common Form Biographical Sketch and a 
 NIH Biographical Sketch Supplement. Both must be created and certified in 
 SciENcv\, and all individuals must have an ORCID iD linked to their eRA 
 Commons account. SciENcv will generate a single\, certified PDF for 
 submission.\n\nIn this hands-on workshop\, we will guide you through the 
 process of completing the NIH Biosketch using SciENcv. Participants will 
 have the opportunity to work on their biosketch during the session and ask 
 questions.\n\nWe will cover:\n\n\n	What’s changing with the NIH Biosketch 
 \n	Creating and certifying the Common Form and Supplement in 
 SciENcv\n	Linking ORCID and eRA Commons accounts\n	Managing publications 
 and research products in SciENcv\n	Tips for navigating known SciENcv issues 
 and avoiding common pitfalls\n	Troubleshooting technical 
 challenges\n\n\nWho should attend:\nInvestigators\, research staff\, and 
 anyone responsible for preparing NIH grant submissions.
LOCATION:Virtual
ORGANIZER;CN="Jessi Gorton":MAILTO:gorton@ohsu.edu
CATEGORIES:Professional Development
UID:LibCal-6248-16209918
URL:https://librarycalendar.ohsu.edu/calendar/workshops/NIH_Biosketch
END:VEVENT
